<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HENDRICKSON SUSPENSION SYSTEMS - MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
            <title>FASTENERS</title>
            <para>Periodically check suspension system fasteners for correct torque. Tighten them to the value found in
                the
                <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>Check the torque of the beam end fasteners after 1,000 miles (1,600 kilometers) of off-road or severe
                service, or 10,000 miles (16,000 kilometers) of on-road service.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Fasteners which do not provide a secure joint between the frame and brackets can cause
                        premature failure of the frame brackets, separation of components, loss of vehicle control and
                        possible personal injury or property damage.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>Tighten fasteners to the values found in the
                <hotlnk document="s03006s_29.xml" xrefid="hl0300604">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
